We will use the formula,

\begin{align*} \text{Proj}_{c}a &= \frac{a\cdot c}{|c|^2} c .\end{align*}

Note that

\[a\cdot c = -9+12+36 = 39\]

and

\[|c|^2 = c\cdot c = 9+16+144 = 169.\]

Hence,

\begin{align*} \text{Proj}_{c}a &= \frac{a\cdot c}{|c|^2} c = \frac{39}{169} c = \frac{3}{13}\begin{bmatrix}
3 \\ -4 \\ 12
\end{bmatrix} .\end{align*}
